main event: A rectangular object passed through 45 degrees of arc in four seconds, observed by Dr. Stillwater and his wife along with other residents in Stillwater.
interesting points: The object had lights along its side and was four times as long as it was wide,It was observed for only 4 seconds,Dr. Stillwater's observation occurred on September 14, 1955,The sighting was classified as a probable meteor sighting by the report,The object traveled back and forth at a moderate speed.
witness description: Dr. Stillwater and his wife with other residents of Stillwater
